ef>)\n:* Running mate: Alex Hirsch, political operative\n* Alex Paterakis, civil engineer and business owner<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/-29-Year-Old-Suburban-Democrat-Running-for-Governor-412357043.html|title=Meet the 29-Year-Old Suburban Democrat Running for Governor|work=[[WMAQ-TV|NBC 5 Chicago]]|last=Schuba|first=Tom|date=January 31, 2017|accessdate=February 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/news/20171204/paterakis-leaves-governor-race-says-without-money-theres-no-path-forward|title=Paterakis leaves governor race, says without money there's 'no path forward'|work=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]|last=Pyke|first=Marni|date=December 4, 2017|accessdate=December 5, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Ameya Pawar]], [[Chicago City Council|Chicago Alderman]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/10/12/pawar-ends-his-campaign-cites-money/|title=Pawar ends his campaign, cites money|last=Miller|first=Rich|date=October 12, 2017|work=[[WMAQ-TV|NBC 5 Chicago]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n:* Running mate: Tyrone Coleman, Mayor of [[Cairo, Illinois|Cairo]]\n\n====Declined====\n* [[Cheri Bustos]], U.S. Representative<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-cheri-bustos-illinois-governor-race-met-0221-20170220-story.html|title=Democratic U.S. Rep. Bustos won't run for Illinois governor in 2018|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|last=Skiba|first=Katherine|date=February 20, 2017|accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Arne Duncan]], former [[United States Secretary of Education]]<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = Arne Duncan, Next Governor of Illinois?|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mercedes-schneider/arne-duncan-next-governor_b_8328410.html|website = The Huffington Post|accessdate = February 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://capitolfax.com/2016/09/21/duncan-says-hes-not-planning-to-run-for-mayor-or-governor/|title=Duncan says he's not planning to run for mayor or gove