ection box total no change\n| votes = 1,324,548\n| percentage = 100\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\nPritzker won 98 of Illinois' counties. Kennedy won two, and Biss also won two.\n\n==Republican primary==\n===Candidates===\n\n====Nominated====\n* [[Bruce Rauner]], incumbent governor<ref name=\":9\"/>\n** Running mate: [[Evelyn Sanguinetti]], incumbent lieutenant governor\n\n====Eliminated in primary====\n* [[Jeanne Ives]], [[Illinois House of Representatives|State Representative]]<ref name=\"Hinz\">Hinz, Greg. \"[http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/20170929/BLOGS02/170929845/abortion-decision-may-spark-challenge-from-gov-rauners-right Did Rauner just uncork a challenge from the right?]\", ''[[Crain's Chicago Business]]'', September 29, 2017. Retrieved September 29, 2017.</ref><ref name=\"Ives Announces\">{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=It's an Ives-Morthland ticket|date=October 28, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]|accessdate=October 28, 2017|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/10/28/its-an-ives-morthland-ticket/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last1=Pearson | first1=Rick | last2=Geiger | first2=Kim | last3=Garcia | first3=Monique | title=Rauner Faces War on Two Fronts as Republican Challenger Ives Attacks | url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-met-bruce-rauner-ives-primary-challenge-20171204-story.html | date=December 5, 2017 | newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]] | accessdate=January 23, 2018}}</ref>\n** Running mate: [[Richard Morthland]], [[Rock Island County, Illinois|Rock Island County]] board member and former state representative\n\n====Withdrew====\n* William J. Kelly, radio host and [[perennial candidate]] (running as an independent)<ref name=\"wjk-taps-tranchant\">{{cite news release | url = https://www.williamjkelly.org/news/kelly-taps-ray-tranchant-for-running-mate-against-rauner | title = Kelly Taps Ray Tranchant For Running Mate Against Rauner | date = 2017-09-05 | publisher = Friends of William J. Kelly | location = Chicago | accessdate = 2017-10-05 }}</ref><ref name=ivesjoins>{{cite web |url=http://www.sj-r.com/news/20171204/ives-joins-governors-race-says-rauner-has-betrayed-our-party|title=Ives joins governor's race, says Rauner has 'betrayed our party'|work=[[The State Journal-Register]]|last=Schoenburg|first=Bernard|date=December 4, 2017|accessdate=December 5, 2017}}</ref>\n** Running mate: [[Brian Leggero]], candidate for Mayor of [[Rockford, Illinois|Rockford]] in 2017<ref name=kellyleggero>{{cite news | url = http://www.wrex.com/story/36525304/2017/10/Wednesday/kelly-picks-legerro-as-running-mate | title = Kelly picks Leggero as running mate | edition = online | work = [[WREX]] | location = Rockford, Illinois | date = 2017-10-04 | first = Michael | last = Poirier | accessdate = 2017-10-05 }}</ref>\n** Former running mate: [[Ray Tranchant]], immigration activist<ref name=\"wjk-taps-tranchant\"/><ref name=\"ng-man-off\">{{cite news | url = http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2017-10-05/catlin-man-gop-gubernatorial-ticket.html | title = Catlin man off GOP gubernatorial ticket | date = 2017-10-05 | first = Tom | last = Kacich | work = [[The News-Gazette (Champaign-Urbana)|The News-Gazette]] | edition = online | location = Champaign, Illinois | accessdate = 2017-10-05 }}</ref>\n\n===Endorsements===\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Jeanne Ives\n| list =\n;Illinois legislators\n* Senator [[Tim Bivins]] (R-[[Dixon, Illinois|Dixon]])<ref name=\"Legislative Endorsements Jan 24 2018\">{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Ives touts legislative endorsements|date=January 24, 2018|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]|url=https://capitolfax.com/2018/01/24/ives-touts-legislative-endorsements}}</ref>\n* Representative [[Peter Breen (Illinois politician)|Peter Breen]] (R-[[Lombard, Illinois|Lombard]])<ref name=\"Legislative Endorsements Jan 24 2018\"/>\n* Senator [[Kyle McCarter]] (R-[[Lebanon, Illinois|Lebanon]])<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bnd.com/news/local/article185352708.html|last=Bustos|first=Joseph|title=McCarter endorses Republican for governor \u2014 and it's not Rauner|date=November 17, 2017|newspaper=[[Belleville News-Democrat]]|accessdate=November 20, 2017}}</ref>\n* Representative [[Margo McDermed]] (R-[[Frankfort, Illinois|Frankfort]])<ref name=\"Legislative Endorsements Jan 24 2018\"/>\n* Representative [[David McSweeney (politician)|David McSweeney]] (R-[[Cary, Illinois|Cary]])<ref name=\"Legislative Endorsements Jan 24 2018\"/>\n* Representative [[Tom Morrison (politician)|Tom Morrison]] (R-[[Palatine, Illinois|Palatine]])<ref name=\"Illinois Family Institute\"/>\n* Representative [[Allen Skillicorn]] (R-[[East Dundee, Illinois|East Dundee]])<ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Skillicorn endorses Ives|date=October 31, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]|accessdate=October 31, 2017|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/10/31/skillicorn-endorses-ives/}}</ref>\n* Representative [[Barbara Wheeler]] (R-[[Crystal Lake, Illinois|Crystal Lake]])<ref name=\"Legislative Endorsements Jan 24 2018\"/>\n; Local officials\n* [[Cook County Board Of Review]] Commissioner Dan Patlak<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/DanPatlak/|title=Log In or Sign Up to View|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Naperville Township, DuPage County, Illinois|Naperville Township Highway Commissioner]] Warren Dixon\n* [[Wheatland Township, Will County, Illinois|Wheatland Township Trustee]] Raquel Mitchell\n;Individuals\n* [[Mike Gallagher (political commentator)|Mike Gallagher]],  radio host and conservative political commentator<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|title=Mike Gallagher joined Dan and Amy to talk about his trip to Chicago in support of Jeanne Ives, and also the fall of Steve Bannon|date=January 10, 2018|newspaper=Chicago's Morning Answer|accessdate=January 11, 2018|url=http://morninganswerchicago.com/2018/01/11/chicagos-morning-answer-show-notes-wednesday-1-10-2018/}}</ref>\n* [[Virginia Halas McCaskey]], principal owner of the [[Chicago Bears]]<ref>{{cite web|l