-for-governor-of-illinois/|title=Nat'l Pro-life Group Endorses Jeanne Ives for Governor of Illinois \u2013 Jeanne Ives For Illinois|website=Ivesforillinois.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Jim Tobin (activist)|Taxpayers United of America]]<ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|url=http://www.taxpayersunitedofamerica.org/latest/tax-accountability-endorses-jeanne-ives-in-illinois-gop-gubernatorial-primary|title=Tax Accountability Endorses Jeanne Ives in Illinois' GOP Gubernatorial Primary|website=Taxpayers United of America|accessdate=January 20, 2018}}</ref>\n;Newspapers and magazines\n* ''[[Daily Journal (Illinois)|Daily Journal]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.daily-journal.com/opinion/editorials/who-is-jeanne-ives/article_3087d54b-335d-5b08-8a44-216c489a82f9.html|title=Who is Jeanne Ives?|work=Daily Journal|date=February 17, 2018}}</ref>\n* ''[[Rockford Register Star]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rrstar.com/opinion/20180310/our-view-republicans-should-give-ives-chance-to-be-governor|title=Our View: Republicans should give Ives a chance to be governor|work=Rockford Register Star|date=March 10, 2018}}</ref>\n* ''[[National Review]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/2018/03/jeanne-ives-illinois-governor-endorsement-rauner-forfeited-conservative-support/|author=National Review Editorial Board|title=Jeanne Ives for Governor|date=March 16, 2018|accessdate=March 16, 2018|newspaper=National Review}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Declined to endorse in primary\n| list =\n;Individuals\n* Congressman [[John Shimkus]] of [[Illinois's 15th congressional district]]. He has announced he will support the Republican nominee in the general election.<ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Shimkus won't endorse in gubernatorial primary|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/11/21/shimkus-wont-endorse-in-gubernatorial-primary/|date=November 21, 2017|accessdate=November 21, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Debates===\n[[Bruce Rauner|Rauner]] and [[Jeanne Ives|Ives]] held their first and only scheduled forum on January 29. Rauner largely ignored his opponent and focused on attacking Speaker [[Mike Madigan]], comparing him to his likely Democratic challenger, [[J. B. Pritzker]]. Ives, on the other hand, attacked Rauner for being an ineffective governor and alienating social conservatives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-met-bruce-rauner-jeanne-ives-debate-20180129-story.html|title=Rauner challenger Ives goes on attack during only forum of Republican governor race|first=Rick Pearson, Kim|last=Geiger|website=chicagotribune.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref> Rauner and Ives were invited by the [[University of Springfield]] to debate a second time, although Rauner declined the invitation.<ref name=\"sj-r.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sj-r.com/news/20180220/democratic-candidates-for-governor-debate-wednesday-at-uis|title=Democratic candidates for governor debate Wednesday at UIS|website=Sj-r.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Bruce<br>Rauner\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Jeanne<br>Ives\n! Undecided\n|-\n| [https://twitter.com/craigrwall/status/974272436702253056 Ogden & Fry (R-Ives)]\n| align=center| March 14, 2018\n| align=center| 787\n| align=center| \u00b1 3.5%\n| {{party shading/Republican}} align=center| '''42%'''\n| align=center| 35%\n| align=center| 23%\n|-\n| [http://paulsimoninstitute.siu.edu/_common/2-27-18-Rauner-Pritzker-Lead-Primary-Polls.pdf Southern Illinois University]\n| align=center| February 19\u201325, 2018\n| align=center| 259\n| align=center| \u00b1 6.0%\n| {{party shading/Republican}} align=center| '''51%'''\n| align=center| 31%\n| align=center| 18%\n|-\n| [http://weaskamerica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Statewide-GOP-Gov-Jan-15.pdf We Ask America]\n| al