summerswont/>\n* [[Chris Taliaferro]], Alderman from Chicago's 29th ward.<ref name=\"Veterans Caucus Endorses\"/><ref=\"Veterans Caucus Members\"/>\n* Flint Taylor, [[Flannigan Township, Hamilton County, Illinois|Flannigan Township]] Trustee and chair of the Hancock County Democratic Party<ref>{{cite web|last=LocalLabs News Service|first=|title=Flannigan Township 2017 Consolidated General Election Results|date=April 12, 2017|newspaper=SE Illinois News: A Dan Proft Political Publication|accessdate=August 25, 2017|url=https://seillinoisnews.com/stories/511103965-flannigan-township-2017-consolidated-general-election-results}}</ref><ref name=\"Cook County\"/><ref name=\"Blue Book\"/>\n* Doris Turner, member of the [[Springfield, Illinois]] City Council and Chair of the Sangamon County Democratic Party.<ref name=\"Cook County\"/>\n* Jim Underwood, member of the [[Richland Community College]] Board of Trustees and chair of the Macon County Democratic Party<ref>{{cite news|last=Voyles|first=Ryan|title=Underwood joins Campbell, Dunning on Richland board|date=April 4, 2017|newspaper=Herald & Review|accessdate=August 25, 2017|url=http://herald-review.com/news/local/underwood-joins-campbell-dunning-on-richland-board/article_6117264b-b579-5c7d-8be0-26c39c59b83b.html}}</ref>\n* [[Gilbert Villegas]], Alderman from Chicago's 36th ward<ref name=\"Veterans Caucus Endorses\">{{cite news|last=Hinton|first=Rachel|title=City Council veterans caucus endorses Pritzker, urges reforms|date=February 22, 2018|accessdate=March 1, 2018|newspaper=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/chicago-politics/city-council-veterans-caucus-endorses-pritzker-urges-reforms/}}</ref><ref name=\"Veterans Caucus Members\">{{cite news|last=Quig|first=A.D.|title=Formation of Veteran Caucus to Be Announced Today|date=February 10, 2016|newspaper=The Daily Line|accessdate=August 14, 2018|url=http://thedailyline.net/chicago/02/10/2016/formation-veteran-caucus-announced-today/}}</ref>\n\n;Individuals\n