-attorney-general-campaign-met-20170919-story.html|accessdate=19 September 2017|newspaper=Chicago Tribune|date=19 September 2017}}</ref>)\n:* Running mate: Alex Hirsch, political operative\n* Alex Paterakis, civil engineer and business owner<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/-29-Year-Old-Suburban-Democrat-Running-for-Governor-412357043.html|title=Meet the 29-Year-Old Suburban Democrat Running for Governor|work=[[WMAQ-TV|NBC 5 Chicago]]|last=Schuba|first=Tom|date=January 31, 2017|accessdate=February 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/news/20171204/paterakis-leaves-governor-race-says-without-money-theres-no-path-forward|title=Paterakis leaves governor race, says without money there's 'no path forward'|work=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]|last=Pyke|first=Marni|date=December 4, 2017|accessdate=December 5, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Ameya Pawar]], [[Chicago City Council|Chicago Alderman]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/10/12/pawar-ends-his-campaign-cites-money/|title=Pawar ends his campaign, cites money|last=Miller|first=Rich|date=October 12, 2017|work=[[WMAQ-TV|NBC 5 Chicago]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n:* Running mate: Tyrone Coleman, Mayor of [[Cairo, Illinois|Cairo]]\n\n====Declined====\n* [[Cheri Bustos]], U.S. Representative<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-cheri-bustos-illinois-governor-race-met-0221-20170220-story.html|title=Democratic U.S. Rep. Bustos won't run for Illinois governor in 2018|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|last=Skiba|first=Katherine|date=February 20, 2017|accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Arne Duncan]], former [[United States Secretary of Education]]<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = Arne Duncan, Next Governor of Illinois?|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mercedes-schneider/arne-duncan-next-governor_b_8328410.html|website = The Huffington Post|accessdate = February 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://capitolfax.com/2016/09/21/duncan-says-hes-not-planning-to-run-for-mayor-or-governor/|title=Duncan says he's not planning to run for mayor or governor|publisher=Capitol Fax|date=September 21, 2016|accessdate=September 21, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Dick Durbin]], U.S. Senator<ref name=willdurbinrun>{{cite news|url=http://chicagotonight.wttw.com/2016/05/20/will-dick-durbin-run-governor-2018|title=Will Dick Durbin Run for Governor in 2018?|work=[[WTTW]]|last=Schutz|first=Paris|date=May 20, 2016|accessdate=May 24, 2016}}</ref><ref name=durbinresponds>{{cite news|url=http://chicagotonight.wttw.com/2016/05/23/dick-durbin-responds-speculation-he-ll-run-governor-2018|title=Dick Durbin Responds to Speculation He\u2019ll Run for Governor in 2018|work=[[WTTW]]|last=Schutz|first=Paris|date=May 23, 2016|accessdate=May 24, 2016}}</ref><ref name=durbinsaysno>{{cite news|url=http://jwcdaily.com/2016/10/27/sen-richard-durbin-says-no-to-governor-race-against-rauner/|title=Durbin Says No to Governor Race|work=Daily North Shore|last=Sadin|first=Steve|date=October 27, 2016|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Mike Frerichs]], [[Illinois Treasurer]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://northernpublicradio.org/post/democrats-ponder-rauners-contender-budget-impasse-continues|title=Democrats Ponder Rauner's Contender As Budget Impasse Continues|work=[[Northern Public Radio]]|last=Mackey|first=Brian|date=June 13, 2016|accessdate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2017-01-08/kacich-frerichs-happy-where-hes.html|title=Frerichs happy where he's at|work=[[The News-Gazette (Champaign-Urbana)|The News-Gazette]]|last=Kacich|first=Tom|date=January 8, 2017|accessdate=January 9, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Valerie Jarrett]], former [[Senior Advisor to the President]]<ref name=\"Vinicky\">{{cite news|url=http://nprillinois.org/post/who-will-take-bruce-rauner-democrats-search-begins-dnc#stream/0|title=Who Will Take On Bruce Rauner? Democrats' Search Begins at DNC|work=[[WUIS|National Public Rad