e web|title = Will Barack Obama Run for Governor of Illinois?|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/will-reynolds/will-barack-obama-run-for_b_9211018.html|website = The Huffington Post|accessdate = February 15, 2016}}</ref><ref name=michellesays/>\n* [[Michelle Obama]], former [[First Lady of the United States]]<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.nationaljournal.com/s/643592?unlock=G9L5A9ZEBOBPMHXQ&mref=homepage-free|title=What's Next for Michelle Obama?|magazine=[[National Journal]]|last=Bruggeman|first=Karyn|date=October 17, 2016|accessdate=October 17, 2016}}</ref><ref name=michellesays>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/04/27/politics/michelle-obama-says-she-wont-run-for-office/|title=Michelle Obama says she won't run for office|work=[[CNN]]|last1=Diaz|first1=Daniella|last2=Couwels|first2=John|date=April 27, 2017|accessdate=April 27, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Penny Pritzker]], former [[United States Secretary of Commerce]]<ref name=durbinsaysno/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/news/sweet-presidents-pal-pritzker-ponders-next-move/|title=Commerce Secretary Pritzker ponders next move|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|last=Sweet|first=Lynn|date=January 15, 2017|accessdate=April 27, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Pat Quinn (politician)|Pat Quinn]], former governor of Illinois ([[Illinois Attorney General election, 2018|Ran for Attorney General]])<ref name=durbinresponds/><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|title = Pat Quinn seeks another shot at re-election, Rauner|url =http://www.politico.com/states/illinois/story/2015/11/pat-quinn-seeks-another-shot-at-re-election-rauner-027597|work=[[Politico]]|last=Korecki|first=Natasha|date=November 5, 2015|accessdate = November 5, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Pat Quinn to run for attorney general|date=October 27, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]|accessdate=October 27, 2017|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/10/27/pat-quinn-to-run-for-attorney-general/}}</ref>\n* [[Heather Steans]], state senator<ref name=durbinresponds/