iss|accessdate=26 July 2017}}</ref>\n* Senator [[William Cunningham (Illinois politician)|Bill Cunningham]] (D-Chicago)<ref>{{cite web|title=State Senator Bill Cunningham Endorses Daniel Biss|url=https://www.danielbiss.com/cunningham-endorses-biss/|website=DanielBiss|accessdate=January 17, 2018}}</ref>\n* Senate president pro tempore [[Don Harmon]] (D-[[Oak Park, Illinois|Oak Park]])<ref>{{cite news|title=Morning Spin: Cook County Democrats to consider endorsing Lisa Madigan successor|author=<!--none credited-->|date=November 3, 2017|accessdate=November 3, 2017|newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-cook-county-democrats-attorney-general-20171103-story.html}}</ref>\n* Senator [[David Koehler]] (D-Peoria)<ref>{{cite web|title=State Sen. Koehler Endorses State Sen. Biss for Governor|url=http://peoriapublicradio.org/post/state-sen-koehler-endorses-state-sen-biss-governor#stream/|website=PeoriaPublicRadio|accessdate=7 July 2017}}</ref>\n* Senator [[Pat McGuire (politician)|Pat McGuire]] (D-Braidwood)<ref>{{cite news|title=Pat McGuire endorses Daniel Biss for governor|last=Ortiz|first=Alex|newspaper=[[The Herald-News]]|location=[[Joliet, Illinois]]|date=August 21, 2017|url=http://www.theherald-news.com/2017/08/20/pat-mcguire-endorses-daniel-biss-for-governor/aavmdtn/|publisher=[[Shaw Media]]|accessdate=August 24, 2017}}</ref>\n* Senator [[John Mulroe]] (D-Chicago)<ref name=\"November 14 Endorsements\">{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Dem candidates announce endorsements|date=November 14, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]|accessdate=November 14, 2017|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/11/14/dem-candidates-announce-endorsements/}}</ref>\n* Senator [[Laura Murphy]] (D-[[Des Plaines, Illinois|Des Plaines]]). Murphy also serves as the Democratic Committeewoman for [[Maine Township, Cook County, Illinois|Maine Township]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/newsletters/illinois-playbook/2017/11/17/sexual-harassment-bill