officeholders\n* Cook County Commissioner [[Jes\u00fas \"Chuy\" Garc\u00eda|Chuy Garc\u00eda]].<ref name=\"CHUY\">{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Chuy Garcia says Kennedy is only Dem who can defeat Rauner|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]|date=September 28, 2017|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/09/28/chuy-garcia-says-kennedy-is-only-dem-who-can-defeat-rauner/|accessdate=September 28, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Lori Lightfoot]], chair of the Chicago Police Accountability Task Force<ref name=\"November 14 Endorsements\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wlsam.com/2017/11/14/kennedy-picks-up-endorsement-of-police-board-president/|title=Kennedy picks up endorsement of Police Board president|date=November 14, 2017|website=WLS-AM 890 - WLS-AM|accessdate=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n* Alderman [[Ricardo Mu\u00f1oz]] of Chicago's 22nd ward.<ref name=\"CHUY\"/>\n;Invididuals\n*[[Dan Aykroyd]], actor and comedian<ref name=\"chicagotribune.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/chicagoinc/ct-met-celeb-governor-0311-chicago-inc-20180309-story.html|title=Dan Aykroyd takes shot at Cook County Assessor Berrios in 'Blues Brothers'-themed ad for Chris Kennedy|first=Kim|last=Janssen|website=Chicagotribune.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Keegan-Michael Key]], comedian and actor<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kennedyforillinois.com/facebook-event/a-night-of-comedy/|title=A Night Of Comedy, With Special Guest Keegan-Michael Key - Chris Kennedy for Illinois|website=Kennedyforillinois.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Larry David]], comedian  and writer<ref name=\"chicagotribune.com\"/>\n*[[Dolores Huerta]],  civil rights and labor union activist{{citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n*[[Barbra Streisand]], singer and actress<ref name=\"chicagotribune.com\"/>\n;Organizations\n* Iroquois County Democratic Central Committee<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2017-04-16/tom-kacich-university-presidents-help-make-sense-nonsense.html|title=University presidents help make sense of nonsense|work=[[The News-Gazette (Champaign-Urbana)|The News-Gazette]]|last=Kacich|first=Tom|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017}}</ref>\n* Southern Illinois Democratic County Chairmen's Association<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kennedyforillinois.com/2017/03/kennedy-receives-endorsement-southern-illinois-democratic-county-chairmens-association/|title=Kennedy Receives Endorsement of Southern Illinois Democratic County Chairmen's Association|work=Kennedy for Illinois|date=March 1, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017}}</ref>\n;Newspapers\n* ''[[Journal Star (Peoria)|Journal Star]] ''<ref>{{cite news|title=Endorsement: Kennedy for governor, Democrats|date=March 2, 2018|newspaper=Journal Star|accessdate=March 7, 2018|url=http://www.pjstar.com/opinion/20180302/endorsement-kennedy-for-governor-democrats}}</ref>\n* ''[[The State Journal-Register]]''<ref>{{cite news |title= Endorsement: For the Democrats, Kennedy for governor |newspaper= The State Journal-Register |accessdate= March 9, 2018 |url= http://www.sj-r.com/opinion/20180309/our-view-for-democrats-kennedy-for-governor}}</ref>\n* ''[[Chicago Tribune]]''<ref>{{cite news |title= Endorsement: For the Democrats, Chris Kennedy |date= February 21, 2018 |newspaper= Chicago Tribune |accessdate= February 21, 2018|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/editorials/ct-edit-kennedy-pritzker-governor-biss-illinois-20180216-story.html}}</ref>\n* ''[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]''<ref>{{cite news|title=Endorsement: Kennedy for governor in Democratic primary|date=February 16, 2018|newspaper=Daily Herald|accessdate=February 16, 2018|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/discuss/20180216/endorsement-kennedy-for-governor-in-democratic-primary}}</ref>}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Declined to endorse for the primary\n| list =\n;U.S. Representatives\n*[[Jan Schakowsky]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Hawley|first=Rachel|title=Representative Jan Schakowsky talks 20 years of progressive politics|url=http://www.northbynorthwestern.com/story/representative-jan-schakowsky-talks-politics-with-/|date=January 25, 2018|accessdate=January 29, 2018|newspaper=[[North by Northwestern]]}}</ref>\n;Organizations\n* Madison County Democratic Party<ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=Pritzker nearly pulls off upset caucus win|url=https://capitolfax.com/2017/09/19/pritzker-nearly-pulls-off-upset-caucus-win/|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=September 30, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Forums===\nThe Illinois LGBTQ Forum: The Democratic Candidates for Governor<ref>[http://www.equalityillinois.us/2017/09/lgbtq-forum-the-democratic-candidates-for-governor/ \"The Illinois LGBTQ Forum: The Democratic Candidates for Governor\"], official website.</ref> was held on December 6, 2017, and organized by Affinity Community Services, the Association of Latinos/as Motivating Action (ALMA), the Equality Illinois Institute, and Pride Action Tank. Candidates who attended included Daniel Biss, Tio Hardiman, Ameya Pawar, J. B. Pritzker, and Chris Kennedy.\n\n[[Whitney M. Young Magnet High School|Whitney Young High School]] hosted the first student-run gubernatorial debate in the United States on October 4, 2017. All 7 then current candidates attended, meaning Daniel Biss, Bob Daiber, Tio Hardiman, Chris Kennedy, Alex Paterakis, Ameya Pawar, and J. B. Pritzker.<ref>[http://chicago.cbslocal.com/2017/10/04/students-stage-gubernatorial-debate/ \"Students on stage for the gubernatorial debate\"], chicago.cbslocal.com.</ref>\n\nThe Illinois chapter of progressive advocacy organization [[Our Revolution]] sponsored a forum at the [[Chicago Teacher's Union]] headquarters on October 8, 2017. Candidates voiced similar opinions on [[single-payer health care]], [[gun control]], and the [[minimum wage]], but differed on a hypothetical state deal with [[Amazon.com|Amazon]] and relationships with powerful Illinois Speaker [[Mike Madigan]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hartz|first1=Taylor|title=Democratic candidates for governor face off in progressive forum|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/news/democratic-candidates-for-governor-face-off-in-progressive-forum/|accessdate=9 October 2017|work=Chicago Sun-Times|date=9 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe Democratic candidates held their first televised debate on January 23.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcchicago.com/blogs/ward-room/watch-the-illinois-democratic-gubernatorial-forum-470814953.html|title=Watch the Full Illinois Democratic Gubernatorial Forum|website=Nbcchicago.vom|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref> All six candidates met again a week later on January 30. The debate was not televised but was uploaded to [[WSIL-TV|WSIL-TV's]] [[YouTube]] channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UZj8_916mjM|title=IL Democratic Gubernatorial Debate at SIU 1-30-18|first=|last=WSIL News|date=January 31, 2018|accessdate=May 22, 2018|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nAnother debate was held on February 21, which was hosted by the [[University of Springfield]].<ref name=\"sj-r.com\"/> [[Christopher G. Kennedy|Chris Kennedy]] did not attend due to a back injury, although all five other candidates participated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/politics/democrats-governor-illinois-debate-livestream-springfield/|title=WATCH: Democrats take the capital city stage for governor debate|website=Chicago.suntimes.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref> Another major debate took place on March 1. It involved issues such as gun control, Blagojevich's tapes, sexual harassment, and relatability.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-met-illinois-democratic-governor-debate-wbez-20180301-story.html|title=Democratic debate: Kennedy says Pritzker used 'the language of racists' on Blagojevich call|first=Rick Pearson, Kim|last=Geiger|website=Chicagotribune.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref> Another debate took place the next day in Springfield. The topics involved Madigan, sexual harassment, among other issues. The spotlight remained on the top contenders: Chris Kennedy, J.B Pritzker, and Daniel Biss.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wgntv.com/2018/03/02/democratic-candidates-for-illinois-governor-face-off-in-debate/|title=Democratic candidates for Illinois governor face off in debate|date=March 3, 2018|website=Wgntv.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nPritzker was criticized for refusing to commit to attend the only live-television debate planned outside the Chicago media market, prompting the debate's cancellation.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Meadows|first1=Jim|last2=Boodhoo|first2=Niala|title=Downstate Debate Cancelled After Pritzker Declines|url=http://peoriapublicradio.org/post/downstate-debate-cancelled-after-pritzker-declines#stream/0|accessdate=7 March 2018|work=Peoria Public Radio|date=20 February 2018|language=en}}</ref> Biss and Kennedy gathered petition signatures to encourage the debate's continuation, and Biss commented that \"JB is borrowing a page from the billionaire playbook, avoiding debates and shunning reporters who ask tough questions.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zorn|first1=Eric|title=Shameful decision by a Downstate TV station allows Pritzker to cancel a debate|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/zorn/ct-perspec-zorn-pritzker-debate-rauner-cancel-0225-20180222-story.html|accessdate=7 March 2018|work=chicagotribune.com|date=23 February 2018}}</ref> Another debate took place on March 14, revolving around topics including Pritzker's newly reported offshore holdings, Illinois House Speaker [[Mike Madigan]], and education. Kennedy and Biss both attacked Pritzker on the offshore businesses, Kennedy \"saying it's like a job interview, and Pritzker lying to get the job\", and Biss saying \"Pritzker did that to avoid taxes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilnews.org/news/state_politics/pritzker-hounded-by-reported-tax-evasion-schemes-in-final-debate/article_270ba74e-27ee-11e8-9ea3-5f7b7b803113.html |title= Pritzker hounded by reported tax evasion schemes in final debate before primary election |author= Cole Lauterbach - Illinois News Network |publisher= |accessdate= May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Daniel<br>Biss\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Chris<br>Kennedy\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| J. B.<br>Pritzker\n! Other\n! Undecided\n|-\n| [https://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/exclusive-new-polll-released-2-days-prior-to-election-477208573.html Victory Research]\n| align=center| March 13\u201316, 2018\n| align=center| 1,204\n| align=center| \u00b1 2.8%\n| align=center| 22%\n| align=center| 26%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''32%'''\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 16%\n|-\n| [https://capitolfax.com/2018/03/12/poll-pritzker-up-by-19-quinn-leads-by-8/ We Ask America]\n| align=center| March 7\u20139, 2018\n| align=center| 1,029\n| align=center| \u00b1 3.1%\n| align=center| 15%\n| align=center| 16%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''35%'''\n| align=center| 1%<ref>Bob Daiber with 1%, Tio Hardiman and Robert Marshall with <1%</ref>\n| align=center| 31%\n|-\n| [http://paulsimoninstitute.siu.edu/_common/2-27-18-Rauner-Pritzker-Lead-Primary-Polls.pdf Southern Illinois University]\n| align=center| February 19\u201325, 2018\n| align=center| 472\n| align=center| \u00b1 4.5%\n| align=center| 21%\n| align=center| 17%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''31%'''\n| align=center| 6%<ref>Tio Hardiman with 2%, Bob Daiber, Robert Marshall, and Terry Getz with 1%, other 1%</ref>\n| align=center| 25%\n|-\n| [https://www.politico.com/story/2018/02/21/illinois-governor-rauner-pritzker-417898 Global Strategy Group (D-Pritzker)]\n| align=center| February 9\u201313, 2018\n| align=center| 802\n| align=center| \u00b1 3.5%\n| align=center| 21%\n| align=center| 23%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=cen