imary/|date=November 21, 2017|accessdate=November 21, 2017|newspaper=[[Capitol Fax]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Debates===\n[[Bruce Rauner|Rauner]] and [[Jeanne Ives|Ives]] held their first and only scheduled forum on January 29. Rauner largely ignored his opponent and focused on attacking Speaker [[Mike Madigan]], comparing him to his likely Democratic challenger, [[J. B. Pritzker]]. Ives, on the other hand, attacked Rauner for being an ineffective governor and alienating social conservatives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/politics/ct-met-bruce-rauner-jeanne-ives-debate-20180129-story.html|title=Rauner challenger Ives goes on attack during only forum of Republican governor race|first=Rick Pearson, Kim|last=Geiger|website=chicagotribune.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref> Rauner and Ives were invited by the [[University of Springfield]] to debate a second time, although Rauner declined the invitation.<ref name=\"sj-r.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sj-r.com/news/20180220/democratic-candidates-for-governor-debate-wednesday-at-uis|title=Democratic candidates for governor debate Wednesday at UIS|website=Sj-r.com|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Bruce<br>Rauner\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Jeanne<br>Ives\n! Undecided\n|-\n| [https://twitter.com/craigrwall/status/974272436702253056 Ogden & Fry (R-Ives)]\n| align=center| March 14, 2018\n| align=center| 787\n| align=center| \u00b1 3.5%\n| {{party shading/Republican}} align=center| '''42%'''\n| align=center| 35%\n| align=center| 23%\n|-\n| [http://paulsimoninstitute.siu.edu/_common/2-27-18-Rauner-Pritzker-Lead-Primary-Polls.pdf Southern Illinois University]\n| align=center| February 19\u201325, 2018\n| align=center| 259\n| align=center| \u00b1 6.0%\n| {{party shading/Republican}} align=center| '''51%'''\n| align=center| 3