{"title_page": "Little Boy (song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 single by KSI}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Little Boy\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| album      =\n| EP         = Disstracktions\n| released   = 13 August 2017\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = August 2017\n| studio     = \n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 2:10\n| label      = [[Island Records|Island]]{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Little Boy\" was originally released independently, but has been licensed to [[Island Records]] since 29 September 2017 due to the song's appearance on KSI's fourth extended play Disstracktions.}}\n| writer     = [[KSI (entertainer)|Olajide Olatunji]]<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| producer   = Zeeshan<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| chronology = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| prev_title = Earthquake\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = Two Birds, One Stone\n| next_year  = 2017\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|YQKEJyDiIZc|\"Little Boy\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Little Boy'''\" is a song by British YouTube personality and rapper [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]. The song is a [[Diss (music)|diss track]] aimed at YouTuber and fellow [[Sidemen]] member Wroetoshaw in response to Wroetoshaw's diss track \"KSI Sucks\". It was released onto [[YouTube]] on 13 August 2017, five days after Wroetoshaw released \"KSI Sucks\", and more than a month later, on 29 September 2017, it was made available for digital download and streaming on all platforms through [[Island Records]] due to its appearance on KSI's fourth extended play (EP) ''Disstracktions.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BZWlvlCBASE/|title=Coming to ITunes, Spotify and Google Play next Friday, 29th September|last=KSI|first=|date=2017-09-22|website=[[Instagram]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 4 August 2017, while on vacation in [[Los Angeles]], KSI announced via [[Twitter]] that he would be leaving the British YouTube group [[Sidemen]]. He tweeted: \"Yeah, I think it's time I move on from the sidemen. The journey has been A LOT of fun, but it's time to move on to bigger things. I'll explain in a video soon, but yeah, this was eventually gonna happen, so I guess now is the best time to say it\".<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=KSIOlajidebt|number=893339490105794560|title=Yeah, I think it's time I move on from the sidemen. The journey has been A LOT of fun, but it's time to move on to bigger things.|date=2017-08-04|access-date=2020-04-20|author=KSI}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=KSIOlajidebt|number=893359939917238272|title=I'll explain in a video soon, but yeah, this was eventually gonna happen, so I guess now is the best time to say it.|date=2017-08-04|access-date=2020-04-20|author=KSI}}</ref> On 6 August, KSI uploaded a video to his YouTube channel titled \"I'm Leaving The Sidemen\" in which he further explained his decision to leave the group. At the start of the video, he cited a fall-out with fellow Sidemen member Ethan Payne (known online as Behzinga) as the reason for him leaving the group, and throughout the video, he continually makes jibes at Payne as well as the rest of the Sidemen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0zeg_RDsn-4|title=I'm Leaving The Sidemen|last=|first=|date=2017-08-06|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/news/ksi-explains-reasons-behind-leaving-sidemen-reveals-new-room-banks-house/33738/p7|title=KSI Explains Reasons Behind Leaving The Sidemen And Reveals New Room At Faze Banks' House|last=|first=|date=2017-08-07|website=Dexerto|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nWhile Payne responded to this by making a diss track against KSI<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://grmdaily.com/video/youtuber-drama-behzinga-sends-ksi|title=There's YouTuber \"Drama\" as Behzinga Sends for KSI|last=|first=|date=2017-08-08|website=[[GRM Daily]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ki1sl4Ad08Q|title=Behzinga - Drama (Official Music Video)|last=|first=|date=2017-08-07|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>, fellow Sidemen member Harry Lewis (known online as Wroetoshaw) decided to also respond with a diss track against KSI. The diss track, titled \"KSI Sucks\", was released onto YouTube on 8 August and has 56 million views, as of April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pmcfL_qLhMo|title=W2S - KSI Sucks (RiceGum & KSI Diss Track) Official Video|last=|first=|date=2017-08-08|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> After responding to Payne with his own diss track titled \"Earthquake\",<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uO0ZNHZ5F1E|title=KSI ft Ricegum - Earthquake (Official Music Video)|last=|first=|date=2017-08-12|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> KSI released the diss track \"Little Boy\" in response to Wroetoshaw on 13 August.\n\n== Promotion ==\nKSI teased the upcoming release of \"Little Boy\" by including a thirty seconds-long snippet of the song at the end of the music video for \"Earthquake\", which was released on 12 August 2017, one day before the release of \"Little Boy\".<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number 82 and the [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK R&B Singles Chart]] at number 39 after the release of the ''Disstracktions'' EP.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48106/ksi/|title=KSI {{!}} full Official Chart History|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/r-and-b-singles-chart/20171006/114/|title=Official R&B Singles Chart Top 40|last=|first=|date=2017-10-06|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video, directed by Jovan Thomas, was filmed at the mansion of American YouTubers [[RiceGum]], [[FaZe Banks]] and Alissa Violet in Los Angeles in August 2017 and was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 13 August 2017. As of April 2020, it has 56 million views, making it KSI's second most-viewed music video on YouTube to date.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YQKEJyDiIZc|title=KSI - Little Boy (Official Music Video)|last=|first=|date=2017-08-13|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/KSIOlajidebt/videos?view=64&sort=p&flow=grid|title=KSI - YouTube|last=|first=|date=|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Response ==\nOn 19 August 2017, six days after KSI released \"Little Boy\", Wroetoshaw uploaded a response diss track titled \"KSI Exposed\" to his YouTube channel. As of April 2020, it has 13 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w-VuZzsZq0c|title=W2S - KSI Exposed (Official Music Video)|last=|first=|date=2017-08-19|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/79079729/credits|title=Disstracktions by KSI|last=|first=|date=2017-09-29|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n* [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n* Zeeshan \u2013 producer\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|87|date=20171006|rowheader=true|accessdate=20 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|82|date=20171006|rowheader=true|accessdate=20 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UKrandb|39|date=20171006|rowheader=true|accessdate=20 April 2020}}\n|}\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Region\n! scope=\"col\" |Date\n! scope=\"col\" |Format\n! scope=\"col\" |Label\n! scope=\"col\" |Ref.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\" |Various\n| 13 August 2017\n| [[Streaming media|Streaming]] ([[YouTube]])\n| [[Self-publishing|Self-released]]\n| <ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n| 29 September 2017\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[Island Records|Island]]\n| <ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/gb/album/disstracktions-ep/1440882143|title=Disstracktions - EP by KSI|last=|first=|date=2017-09-29|website=[[Apple Music]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of diss tracks#YouTube|List of diss tracks \u00a7 YouTube]]\n\n== Notes ==\n<references group=\"upper-alpha\" responsive=\"1\"></references>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YQKEJyDiIZc Music video] on [[YouTube]]\n* [https://genius.com/Ksi-little-boy-lyrics Lyrics of the song] at [[Genius (website)|Genius]]\n\n{{KSI}}\n[[Category:2017 songs]]\n[[Category:2017 singles]]\n[[Category:Diss tracks]]\n[[Category:Island Records singles]]\n[[Category:KSI (entertainer) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by KSI (entertainer)]]\n[[Category:YouTube music videos]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 single by KSI}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Little Boy\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| album      =\n| EP         = Disstracktions\n| released   = 13 August 2017\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = August 2017\n| studio     = \n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 2:10\n| label      = [[Island Records|Island]]{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Little Boy\" was originally released independently, but has been licensed to [[Island Records]] since 29 September 2017 due to the song's appearance on KSI's fourth extended play Disstracktions.}}\n| writer     = [[KSI (entertainer)|Olajide Olatunji]]<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| producer   = Zeeshan<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| chronology = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| prev_title = Earthquake\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = Two Birds, One Stone\n| next_year  = 2017\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|YQKEJyDiIZc|\"Little Boy\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Little Boy'''\" is a song by British YouTube personality and rapper [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]. The song is a [[Diss (music)|diss track]] aimed at YouTuber and fellow [[Sidemen]] member Wroetoshaw in response to Wroetoshaw's diss track \"KSI Sucks\". It was released onto [[YouTube]] on 13 August 2017, five days after Wroetoshaw released \"KSI Sucks\", and more than a month later, on 29 September 2017, it was made available for digital download and streaming on all platforms through [[Island Records]] due to its appearance on KSI's fourth extended play (EP) ''Disstracktions.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BZWlvlCBASE/|title=Coming to ITunes, Spotify and Google Play next Friday, 29th September|last=KSI|first=|date=2017-09-22|website=[[Instagram